x4freetext: Two surface barrier silicon detectors mounted
symmetrically at 55 degree were used to detect protons
from the 12C(d,p)13C reaction leading to the ground
state of 13C for which the analysing powers are
accurately known.The detectors used were pairs of solid
state detectors forming dE-E telescopes,two of which
were placed 10 degree apart on each of two arms in the
scattering chamber.An energy resolution of 50 keV was
obtained.The dE-E arrangement,consisting of a surface
barrier passing detector and a lithium drifted silicon
bulk stopping detector,was used for particle
identification in conjunction with an analogue
The beam polarisations were measured using a 100 mu-g/
The self-supporting targets were manufactured by
resistive evaporation of SiO2 enriched in 29Si or 30Si,
